# CATSHY — Threat Intelligence Platform
# Cursor AI Project Rules

## Project Overview
Self-hosted Threat Intelligence Platform (TIP) for cybersecurity analysts.
Production target: Kali Linux (native systemd) or Docker.

## Tech Stack
### Frontend
- React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- TanStack Query for data fetching
- React Router v6 for routing
- Recharts for analytics/charts
- @react-three/fiber + drei for 3D globe visualization
- Framer Motion for animations

### Backend
- FastAPI (async) + Python 3.12
- PostgreSQL 16 (asyncpg) with full-text search
- Redis 7 for caching + Celery broker
- Celery for background task processing
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 (async) + Alembic for migrations
- JWT auth with bcrypt password hashing

## Architecture
```
src/                    # React frontend
├── components/         # Reusable UI components
│   ├── ui/            # shadcn/ui primitives
│   ├── layout/        # AppShell, Sidebar, TopBar
│   ├── dashboard/     # Dashboard widgets
│   └── global-threats/ # Threat map components
├── contexts/          # React contexts (Auth)
├── hooks/             # Custom hooks (useApi, useAuth, useFilters)
├── lib/               # Utilities (api client, cn helper)
├── pages/             # Route pages
└── types/             # TypeScript interfaces

backend/               # FastAPI backend
├── app/
│   ├── core/          # Security, dependencies, exceptions
│   ├── models/        # SQLAlchemy models (user, intel, operations, system)
│   ├── routers/       # API endpoints
│   ├── services/      # Business logic (ingestion, scoring, matching)
│   ├── middleware/     # Audit logging
│   └── tasks/         # Celery background tasks
├── alembic/           # Database migrations
└── tests/             # Test suites
```

## Role System
Roles: system_owner | team_admin | team_member | user
- Roles stored in `user_roles` table (NOT on users table)
- `RequireRole` dependency for endpoint protection
- Frontend checks via `useAuth().hasRole()`

## Key Conventions
- All datetime values use `datetime.now(timezone.utc)` (never `datetime.utcnow()`)
- SQLAlchemy models use `default=list` / `default=dict` (not `default=[]` / `default={}`)
- All CRUD endpoints require authentication via `get_current_user` dependency
- Frontend uses semantic Tailwind tokens from CSS variables (--primary, --background, etc.)
- API client at `src/lib/api.ts` handles dev-mode fallback when no backend detected
- Intel pipeline: fetch → normalize → dedup → enrich → correlate → score → explain → campaign → stats

## Database
- Workspace-scoped multi-tenancy on all data tables
- Dedup via SHA-256 hash per workspace
- Full-text search via PostgreSQL tsvector columns
- Observable normalization (IP, domain, URL, hash, CVE)

## Security
- JWT tokens with short TTL (30 min access, 7 day refresh)
- Rate limiting (Redis-backed for multi-worker)
- Brute-force detection with lockout
- SSRF protection on source fetching
- Audit logging on all state-changing actions
- No secrets in frontend code

## Testing
- Backend: pytest with async support
- Frontend: Vitest
- E2E: Python requests-based test suite

## Deployment
- Primary: Kali Linux with systemd services + Nginx
- Alternative: Docker Compose (postgres + redis + api + celery + nginx)
- Config via .env file (see deploy/.env.example)
